      <section id="id1168921421630">
        <title>Assessment</title>
        <para id="id1168923573712">
          <emphasis effect="bold">LEARNING OUTCOME 1: </emphasis>
          <emphasis effect="bold">CREATING, INTERPRETING AND PRESENTING</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para id="id1168923483722">The learner will be able to create, interpret and present work in each of the art forms.</para>
        <section id="id1168923986595">
          <title>Assessment Standard</title>
          <para id="id1168923592865">We know this when the learner:</para>
          <para id="id1168921053201">1.6 uses voice, body and found or made instruments to explore sounds and silence related to walking, running, and skipping note values, in order to explore rhythms and to create sound pictures;</para>
          <para id="id1168923955072">1.7 composes and presents a short rhythmic pattern that has crotchets, crochet rests, minims and minim rests through body percussion;</para>
          <para id="id1168918306319">1.8 makes in various tone colours, a simple wind instrument such as a Kazoo or Tshikona / Dinaka pipes, or percussion instruments such as shakers;</para>
          <para id="id1168921383852">1.9 creates and presents melodies using voice and sound and natural instruments to demonstrate difference in pitch and note values.</para>
        </section>
